The newly renovated Ezeag­bogu Football ground will host the next round games of the Ikukuoma Mbaise Unity Football Competition sched­uled to commence January 21, 2022 (today). Obize will slug it out with their Ife/Chokoneze/ Akpode counterparts in the opening match while Eziu­do will lock horns with Ot­ulu/Agunzeze in the second game on January 22. Defending Champions Okpofe/Ezeagbogu will be­gin their title defence with a crunchy clash against Ibeku. BREAKING: 3SC GM, Rasheed Balogun Dies At 62 Dollar Rain On Super Eagles By FG, Dangote, Otedola, Others Mbaise football power house, Enyiogugu, will take on Oru/Na Lude while Nnarambia will host Okiri­ka Nwenkwo. Obama/Umu­nama takes on Obohia in the last game of the round. Speaking ahead of the games holding at the home town of the cup donor and sponsor, Dr. Summers Nwokie, team manager of Nnarambia, Finiel Ebuka, said he is grateful to the do­nor for providing the youths of Mbaise the platform to showcase their talents with the competition. He recalled that last year, the competition provided opportunity to five youths to be invited by top clubs in the country. “The players are currently undergoing intensive train­ing”, he disclosed. Organisers however ad­monished participating clubs to ensure that they ar­rived match venue at least two hours before kickoff time. POLL Cup donor High Chief Summers Nwokie revealed that the Foundation will in future extend the tourna­ment to all the Local Gov­ernment Areas in Owerri zone to afford the youths the opportunity to engage their energy in meaning­ful ventures so as to assist in the development of the zone before he could extend the tournament to the state level. Director General of the foundation, Julius Nneji, disclosed that already ar­rangement has been put in place for coaches of clubs in the country to attend the competition at various stages of the competition to scout for young players into their clubs.